\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Nov 14, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ocu1665702763109.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ocu1665702763109.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ocu1665702763109.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ocu1665702763109\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ocu1665702763109__compile_development_objects_17449\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When you compile development objects, Uniface checks the definition, syntax, and\n    integrity of the object, generates descriptors, and stores the compiled object, either on the\n    file system or in the Repository.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ocu1665702763109__li_d1634e1_d1635e1_d1636e1\">To compile and build all objects in a Project, click the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile</span> command in the Project Editor.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ocu1665702763109__li_d1637e1_d1638e1_d1639e1\">To compile a Main Development Object and all its children, choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile</span> in the current editor.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"section result\" id=\"ocu1665702763109__topic_d4157e1_d4158e1_d4159e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ocu1665702763109__p_d4160e1_d4161e1_d4162e1\">The Compiler Output tab displays compilation messages.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ocu1665702763109__p_d4163e1_d4164e1_d4165e1\">The Compiled Module Navigator displays a list of the compiled ProcScript Modules that indicates whether they are local or inherited.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ocu1665702763109__p_d4166e1_d4167e1_d4168e1\">The generated runtime objects are stored as resource files in object-specific subdirectories of the user data directory.</p>\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"ocu1665702763109__note_cmw_f1b_bzb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> You can also use shortcut keys\n          <kbd class=\"ph userinput\">Ctrl+F7</kbd> to compile a current object and\n          <kbd class=\"ph userinput\">Ctrl+Shift+F7</kbd> to compile and test a current object.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530538\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530538\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Compile Development Objects Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Nov 14, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 When you compile development objects, Uniface checks the definition, syntax, and integrity of the object, generates descriptors, and stores the compiled object, either on the file system or in the Repository. To compile and build all objects in a Project, click the Compile command in the Project Editor. To compile a Main Development Object and all its children, choose Compile in the current editor. The Compiler Output tab displays compilation messages. The Compiled Module Navigator displays a list of the compiled ProcScript Modules that indicates whether they are local or inherited. The generated runtime objects are stored as resource files in object-specific subdirectories of the user data directory. Tip: You can also use shortcut keys Ctrl+F7 to compile a current object and Ctrl+Shift+F7 to compile and test a current object. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}